  "body": "The elasticsearch example (production cluster) fails on Kubernetes 1.1.x due to an invalid volume decription in the replication controller files.\n\n``` bash\n$ kubectl create -f examples/elasticsearch/production_cluster/es-master-rc.yaml\nerror validating \"examples/elasticsearch/production_cluster/es-master-rc.yaml\": error validating data: found invalid field source for v1.Volume; if you choose to ignore these errors, turn validation off with --validate=false\n```\n\n``` bash\n$ kubectl create -f examples/elasticsearch/production_cluster/es-client-rc.yaml\nerror validating \"examples/elasticsearch/production_cluster/es-client-rc.yaml\": error validating data: found invalid field source for v1.Volume; if you choose to ignore these errors, turn validation off with --validate=false\n```\n\n``` bash\n$ kubectl create -f examples/elasticsearch/production_cluster/es-data-rc.yaml\nerror validating \"examples/elasticsearch/production_cluster/es-data-rc.yaml\": error validating data: found invalid field source for v1.Volume; if you choose to ignore these errors, turn validation off with --validate=false\n```\n\nI was able to fix this by updating the volume description (PR incoming).\n\n``` diff\n-      - name: storage\n-        source:\n-          emptyDir: {}\n+      - emptyDir:\n+          medium: \"\"\n+        name: \"storage\"\n```\n",
